cs.DB, cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.CC. 

This paper deals with the problem of evaluating conjunctive queries against guarded first-order theories, which is a fundamental problem in database theory and description logic. Therefore, cs.DB (Databases) and cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also involves complexity analysis and finite-model property, which are common topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper introduces new techniques for investigating finite guarded bisimilar covers of hypergraphs and relational structures, which may be relevant to cs.CC (Computational Complexity).
